<HEADLINE> Mexico to Request OPEC for Maintaining Production Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Mexico will request the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) during its
next ministerial meeting in Vienna, to continue with the
production cuts, said an official source on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Energy Ministry of Mexico, a country which
is not a member of the OPEC, said that during Wednesday morning's
meeting, Vice Minister of Politics and Development Jorge Chavez
would participate in the meeting as the Mexican representative.
</P>
<P>
Mexico, which agreed to reduce its exportation volume until
March of the year 2000, by 325,000 barrels of crude per day, will
only participate in the meeting as an observer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
