<HEADLINE> Bosnian President Woos Kuwaiti Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Visiting President of
Bosnia and Herzegovina Alija Izetbegovic on Tuesday invited
Kuwaiti companies and businessmen to invest more money in his
country.
</P>
<P>
"The objective behind my visit to Kuwait is to invite
companies to take part in the privatization process of my
country," Izetbegovic told a press conference here.
</P>
<P>
He said that he had conveyed the request to Kuwaiti Emir Jaber
Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
The Bosnian president, who arrived here Monday on a three-day
visit, held talks earlier in the day with Jaber on ways of
boosting bilateral ties and issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait was among the first countries to recognize Bosnia and
Herzegovina as an independent state. The two countries established
diplomatic relations in January 1993.
</P>
<P>
Izetbegovic last visited Kuwait in 1993, when he held talks
with Jaber on the situation in Bosnia and means of solving the
Bosnian-Serb conflict.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Bosnia are also bound by several cooperative
agreements. The two sides signed in 1997 an agreement to
encourage and protect investment in both countries.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Kuwait Fund for Arab Economic Development extended 6
million Kuwait dinars (19.8 million U.S. dollars) in loans to the
Bosnia Bank for the rebuilding and development of the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
