<HEADLINE> EU Concerned Over Situation in East, West Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) said
Tuesday that it "remains gravely concerned over the humanitarian
situation in East Timor, particularly, in West Timor".
</P>
<P>
The 15-nation bloc reiterated its earlier appeals for allowing
immediate safe access for international humanitarian organizations
to both East and West Timor. "Refugees in West Timor must be free
to decide themselves whether they want to return to East Timor,"
the EU said in a presidency declaration released in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
The European Union also praises the contribution of those UN
member states who have given troops and material support to the
International Force. "The participation of regional states is
especially important for the success of the operation," it said.
</P>
<P>
"We wish to pay tribute those Asian and, in particular, ASEAN
states who have contributed to the establishment of the
international force. It clearly shows their interest in the
maintenance of peace and security in the region," the EU said in
the declaration.
</P>
<P>
As the EU presidency on behalf of the European Union, Finland
said in the statement that the progress in the development of the
International Force in East Timor shows the willingness of the
international community to find a peaceful and lasting solution to
the question of East Timor based on the self-determination of the
people of East Timor. "Fear is giving way for hope in East Timor,"
it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
