<DOCNO> XIE19990922.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Cabinet Approves Agro-industry Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet Tuesday
approved in principle the master plan framework for the country's
agro-industry development over the next five years up to 2004.
</P>
<P>
A budget of 32.97 billion baht (824.2 million U.S. dollars)
will be earmarked for the plan, with the Industry Ministry
authorized to coordinate programs with other agencies.
</P>
<P>
The development plan will cover the agro-industry and export
promotion, import substitution and cottage industry processing.
</P>
<P>
With 26 operating plans, it is expected to promote raw material
and product development, production efficiency, technology
upgrading, research and development, marketing competitiveness and
personnel development.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobs in the industry is forecast to increase by
between 600,000 and 700,000.
</P>
<P>
Agro-industry production could earn the country 389 billion
baht (9.72 billion dollars) a year from exports, making huge dent
in Thailand's lingering trade deficit which stands at 4.9 billion
dollars in the first seven months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
