<HEADLINE> Nepali FM Stresses Good Ties With China, India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Foreign Minister Ram
Sharan Mahat said Tuesday that Nepal has maintained cordial and
cooperative relations with India and China on the basis of good
neighborliness while holding high the country's national interest.
</P>
<P>
Responding to questions from MPs at the House of
Representatives Tuesday, Mahat said Nepal is alert not to allow
the Nepalese territory to be used for any activities directed
against China. He also reiterated Nepal's support to "one China"
policy.
</P>
<P>
Referring to arguments that failure to implement the provisions
made in the treaty on integrated development of the Mahakali river
for preparing the detailed project report within six months after
the signing of the treaty will bring the validity of the treaty
under question, Mahat said these arguments are not based on facts.
</P>
<P>
Nepal and India had a plan to make joint efforts to utilize the
common Mahakali river, but the plan has been delayed because of
some technical problems.
</P>
<P>
Stating that the Mahakali Treaty has been signed bearing in
mind Nepal's national priority, Mahat said a joint office of both
countries is to be set up in Kathmandu soon to work on the
preparation of the detailed project report.
</P>
<P>
Mahat told parliament that discussions are being held with
India on making necessary arrangements for entry registration to
carry out monitoring on Nepal-India border without affecting the
cross border movement of people and goods.
</P>
<P>
During Indian foreign minister's visit to Nepal earlier this
month, the foreign ministers of the two countries agreed to make
joint efforts to curb border criminal activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
