<HEADLINE> Italy's Service Sector Grows But No New Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The Italian service sector, the
country's fastest-growing industry, will not create any more jobs
in the short-term, despite picking up speed in the second quarter
of 1999, according to a report by Isae, the Institute for Economic
Studies and Analysis.
</P>
<P>
"Businesses saw a marked improvement in demand and turnover in
the second quarter, taking into account seasonal increases," the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The Italian government's economic think-tank said the service
sector would see short-term increases in sales prices and demand,
and forecast that turnover would remain stable in the next
quarter.
</P>
<P>
However, in spite of good short-term prospects, Isae said the
service industry would not create any more jobs in the third
quarter.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the marketing industry will be the
only sector to see an increase in payroll figures, while the
technology industry is expected to register the sharpest drop.
</P>
