<HEADLINE> Bell Atlantic Acquires Vodafone For Wireless Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Bell Atlantic, the U.S.
largest local telephone company, agreed Tuesday to acquire
mobile phone network of Vodafone AirTouch in its effort to
create a wireless network.
</P>
<P>
The wireless phone alliance will be able to serve more than
90 percent of the U.S. population with digital technology. The
agreement will combine Bell Atlantic's East Coast network with
Vodafone's West Coast network, enabling customers to use their
wireless phones almost anywhere in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Bell Atlantic will give Vodafone a 45 percent stake in the
new company in exchange for Vodafone's 15 billion-U.S.-dollar
wireless network. The new alliance will have assets of 28
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The agreement came after AT&AMP;T Corp., the U.S. largest long
distance phone company, formed a global alliance with British
Telecom to link their wireless telephone operations, providing
wireless services in 17 countries with a combined customer base
of 41 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
