<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia Association for
Chambers of Commerce and Industry Tuesday urged to increase trade
with its neighbor of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The Association Chairman George Chabwera said his country's
annual imports from Kenya remained at six million U.S. dollars for
the last three years, while Zambia's annual exports to Kenya
increased from two million dollars in 1994 to four million last
year.
</P>
<P>
He told a visiting delegation from Kenya Association of
Manufacturers that the common tariffs being put in place by the
Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA) will not
make sense if inter-African trade is not promoted.
</P>
<P>
Chabwera urged the delegation to explore investment in his
country.
</P>
<P>
Head of the Kenyan delegation Kulwant Chadha said the bilateral
trade is being hindered by the problem of transportation.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to improve the transportation system to
enhance the trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
