<HEADLINE> CPC Mouthpiece Hails Deepening of SOE Reform (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The decision by the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) on the reform of
state-owned enterprises (SOEs) has profound timely and historical
significance, says a People's Daily editorial to be published on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Marking the conclusion of the 4th Plenum of the 15th CPC
Central Committee, the editorial urges that a new door be opened
for the reform and development of the SOEs.
</P>
<P>
It notes that on the eve of the 50th anniversary of the
founding of new China, the CPC Central Committee Decision on
Issues Related to State-Owned Enterprise Reforms and Development
won the approval of the plenum participants. Jiang Zemin, general
secretary of the CPC Central Committee, made an important speech
at the plenum, which was the first special meeting held by the CPC
Central Committee to study reforms and development of the SOEs.
</P>
<P>
The decision summarizes experience with SOE development over
the past two decades and defines guidelines and major policies and
measures for reforms and growth of the state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"The decision is an important milestone in the history of both
the development of SOEs and the economic development of our
country," the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
It points out that SOEs have always played a very important
role in China's economic and social development. It says that
invigoration of the SOEs is both a crucial economic issue in
regard to the health and long-term growth of the national economy
and a crucial political issue in terms of the fate of the
socialist system.
</P>
<P>
At a time when international political and economic situation
is unstable, sciences and technology are advancing rapidly and
international competition is intensifying, national power has
become the key element of a country's future, it says.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that the SOEs are the major pillars of the
economy and major forces in the modernization drive of the country.
Therefore, to enlarge China's economic and defense capabilities
and reinforce the unity of the people, the state-owned sector
should always be expanding and growing stronger.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
