any "extra constitutional means to topple a government," Mushahid
said it was in response to Pakistani opposition leaders who have
been crawling and cringing towards Washington to destabilize a
constitutionally-elected government.
</P>
<P>
He also criticized the opposition for urging the International
Monetary Fund (IMF) to cut off its financial assistance to
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
His remarks came after a recent statement of Imran Khan, leader
of Pakistan Tehrik-e-Insaf, which called for the suspension of IMF
aid to Pakistan to "punish Nawaz Sharif for his dictatorial style
of government."
</P>
<P>
"Seeking self-reliance is different from seeking stoppage of
aid under already signed agreements," Hussain said. 
