<HEADLINE> CPC Mouthpiece Hails Deepening of SOE Reform (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It points out that pushing forward reforms and development of
the SOEs is an important task for the CPC and a honorable mission
for the current generation.
</P>
<P>
It notes that the CPC Central Committee's decision has set the
goals for the SOE reforms in the years to come. The decision also
puts forward ten guidelines for the reforms and development. The
decision particularly emphasizes that the CPC's leadership over
the SOE reforms must be strengthened, which requires fostering a
high-quality management team.
</P>
<P>
In order to implement the spirit of the plenum of the CPC
Central Committee, the editorial calls for all the CPC members,
especially party leaders, to earnestly study the decision. It also
calls for officials at all levels to work diligently to find
solutions for major problems in the SOE reforms.
</P>
<P>
"We will by no means pursue privatization," it says, stressing
that the SOE reforms must stick to the basic economic system with
public ownership as the main form of ownership and other forms of
ownership developing simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
It says that reform and development of the SOEs essentially
means that continuous improvements must be made in the state-owned
sector, which should have increased presence and power of control
in a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
It notes that the plenum of the CPC Central Committee has set
the year 2010 as the target for SOEs. This is a practical and
scientific choice based on the correct assessment of the situation
of SOE reforms. It asks officials to combine short-term goals with
long-term goals during the process of the SOE reform.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says good opportunities exist now for reforms and
development of the SOEs. "We will surely create a new situation of
reforms and development of the SOEs if we earnestly implement the
spirit of the 15th CPC National Congress and the 4th Plenum of the
15th CPC Central Committee," it says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
