<HEADLINE> WHO Pledges Support for Health Research In Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization
(WHO) Wednesday pledged its support for health research in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Ebrahim Samba, WHO regional director for Africa, said in a
statement that his organization supported the research to solve
health problems plaguing Africa.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a health workshop in Harare, Samba regretted that
health research was being given low priority in Africa at a time
when health managers needed good research information to enable
them to make correct decision in formulating health policies.
</P>
<P>
The WHO official called for closer collaboration between
healthy policy makers and technicians in research institutions.
</P>
<P>
He also called on African countries to put in place mechanism
dealing with emergency situation.
</P>
<P>
Such a measure was imperative in those areas prone to both
natural and man-made disasters such as drought, floods and civil
conflicts, said Samba.
</P>
<P>
Emergency preparedness programs developed by various countries
should be able to predict so as to really respond to emergency
situation, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
