<HEADLINE> India Ready for Talks With Pakistan: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee Wednesday said India was ready to hold talks with
Pakistan in a positive and peaceful atmosphere but warned against
any misadventure along the border.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to hold dialogue for peace with Islamabad if a
conducive atmosphere is created for it," he told a heavily
attended election campaign rally in Barh of Bihar state.
</P>
<P>
"We do not want war, but we won whenever it was thrust on us by
Pakistan," he said, adding any misadventure on India's border
would be firmly dealt with.
</P>
<P>
Indicating that Pakistan was once again planning to rake up
Kashmir issue at several international fora, he said, "India is
firm on its stand that Kashmir is an integral part of the country
and we will in no circumstances compromise on this issue."
</P>
</TEXT>
