<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition Calls for New General Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh Nationalist
Party (BNP)-led opposition alliance has called for a dawn-to-dusk
hartal (general strike) on October 3 to protest at the
government's move to hold Upazila (sub-district) polls without
their participation and to demand a fresh voter list.
</P>
<P>
The call for the nationwide hartal was made during separate
rallies in the capital Wednesday of the BNP, Jatiya Party (the
National Party), Jamaat-e-Islami and Islami Okiya Jote (Islami
Solidarity Front).
</P>
<P>
The opposition also demanded cancellation of the "fake" voter
identity cards as well as resignation of the government.
</P>
<P>
The four-party alliance also called for an identical "seize
program" around the Election Commission on September 30, demanding
the resignation of the chief election commissioner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
