<HEADLINE> India Expects Pak to Prevent Crossing Line of Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- India said Wednesday it
expects Pakistan to prevent any intended crossing of the Line of
Control (LoC) or the International Border in Jammu and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
In the context of reports appearing in the Pakistani press
regarding the intention of the so-called Jammu and Kashmir
Liberation Front to cross the LoC in Jammu and Kashmir, Deputy
High Commissioner of Pakistan Akbar Zeb was summoned to the
Ministry of External Affairs Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
A foreign office spokesman said that the Pakistani envoy was
asked to convey to his government "their clear obligation for
ensuring the inviolability and sanctity of the LoC, which is
crucial for the maintenance of tranquillity and security."
</P>
<P>
He was also told that Pakistan would be responsible for any
consequences which might result from its failure to do so.
