<HEADLINE> Gold, Silver Prices Shoot Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Gold and silver prices rose
steeply Wednesday on the bullion market in Mumbai (Bombay) with
the yellow metal skyrocketing by 100 rupees (2.33 U.S. dollars)
per ten grams and silver rallying by 105 rupees (2.44 U.S.
dollars) per kilogram.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold jumped up 100 rupees (2.33 U.S. dollars) to close
at 4,150 rupees (96.51 U.S. dollars) per ten grams as against the
last close of 4,050 rupees (94.19 U.S. dollars). 22-carat gold
was nominally quoted smartly higher at 3,840 rupees (89.30 U.S.
dollars) from 3,745 rupees (87.09 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (.999 fineness) opened firm at 8,125
rupees (188.95 U.S. dollars) per kg but later reacted down
moderately and closed at 8,075 rupees (187.79 U.S. dollars),
showing a smart rise of 105 rupees (2.44 U.S. dollars) over the
last close of 7,970 rupees (185.35 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) firmed up by 115 rupees (2.67 U.S.
dollars) to 7,955 rupees (185 U.S. dollars) per kg from 7,840
rupees (182.33 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
