<HEADLINE> CPPCC Should Play Greater Role in China: President  Jiang (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
has said that the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) should and is fully capable of playing a
greater role in the affairs of the nation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks in a speech today at a meeting marking
the 50th anniversary of the founding of the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
Senior Chinese leader Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu
Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing took part in this afternoon's
meeting.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Jiang recalled the establishment of the CPPCC
and its contribution to the founding of the People's Republic of
China, the post-war economic recovery, as well as the reform and
opening up in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that "the CPPCC is a great innovation of the
Chinese Communist Party which integrates Marxist-Leninist theory
on the united front with China's actual conditions."
</P>
<P>
As an institution of democratic consultation and an
organization of the united front, Jiang said "the CPPCC has played
and will continue to play an important role in China's political,
economic and cultural activities."
</P>
<P>
The president stressed that "upholding the leadership of the
Chinese Communist Party is a fundamental guarantee for success in
efforts to consolidate and develop the patriotic united front and
is the primary political prerequisite for success in China's
multiparty cooperation."
</P>
<P>
"In handling relations between the Chinese Communist Party and
the democratic parties, we shall continue to follow the principle
of long-term coexistence, mutual supervision, sincere treatment in
dealings with each other and the sharing of weal or woe," Jiang
said.
