<HEADLINE> Vietnam Signs Cleaner Production Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has made a commitment
to environmental protection by signing the International
Declaration on Cleaner Production of the United Nations
Environment Program (UNEP), the Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Minister of Science, Technology and Environment Chu
Tuan Nha signed the convention here Wednesday in the witness of
UNEP Regional Director for Asia and the Pacific Nirmal Andrews.
</P>
<P>
The convention, which was formulated by UNEP and made public at
its fifth international seminar in the Republic of Korea last
year, aims to raise awareness of the urgency of current
environmental problems and the concept of a preventive strategy as
a preferred solution.
</P>
<P>
The convention also seeks to renew and intensify the commitment
to cleaner production by society and community leaders, and
promote further international cooperation and technology transfer.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam, the VNA said, has always attached importance to
environmental protection and sustainable development. Vietnam's
National Assembly adopted a law on environmental protection in
December 1993, and the Vietnamese government has issued a series
of legal documents to guide economic development along the
direction of rational use of natural resources and protection of
the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
