<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People's Consultative Group Playing Important Role (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua)-- The Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), the country's major group of
political advisors, has made an important contribution to the
establishment and development of the New China and peaceful
reunification of the motherland, according to Chen Jinyu, the
Deputy Secretary-general of the CPPCC's National Committee.
</P>
<P>
At the first CPPCC Plenary Session, September 21-30, 1949, the
tasks for the founding of the People's Republic of China as the
will of the Chinese people was discussed, with CPPCC exercising
power of the National People's Congress, which had not yet been
established.
</P>
<P>
The Common Program of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, Organic (organization) Law of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, and the Organic Law of
the Central People's Government were passed.
</P>
<P>
The Constitution of the PRC allows for the system of the multi-
party cooperation and political consultation led by the Communist
Party of China to exist and develop for a long time to come.
Whenever the CPPCC is consulted for decision-making advice or the
implementation of State policies, it holds discussions to listen
to different views to ensure that all State policies and
regulations are complete and sound.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five decades, the CPPCC National Committee
members has made nearly 40,000 proposals, almost half of them
pertaining to economic development, said Chen.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990922.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
