<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People's Consultative Group Playing Important Role (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After China began its reforms and opening up in the late 1970s,
the CPPCC became more active in the country's political life.
CPPCC National Committee members have made suggestions on many
important issues like the Three Gorges Water Control Project,
Shanghai's Pudong New Area, and poverty eradication. In addition
to these political consultations, its functions include
supervising government operations and participating in
deliberations on and the administration of State affairs, Chen
said.
</P>
<P>
The reunification of the motherland is another of its key areas.
The CPPCC National Committee has repeatedly announced that it
supports the government's stand on the Taiwan issue and condemns
the separatist remarks and actions of certain people in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee members in Hong Kong had worked
hard for the return of Hong Kong to the motherland and now those
in Macao are engaged in the return of Macao.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee has increased relations with
institutions elsewhere in the world and established ties with 108
organizations in 72 countries, and 4 international and regional
organizations.
</P>
<P>
"With the development of the socialist market economy and
socialist democratic politics in China in the next century, the
CPPCC will have to bear more responsibility," the deputy-secretary
general says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
