<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Says Kosovo Protection Corps Attempt to Legalize KLA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Russia said Wednesday that
the formation of a Kosovo Protection Corps (KPC) with the
functions of an emergency situations organization was a clear
attempt to legalize part of the Kosovo rebels' military formations.
</P>
<P>
The statement by the Russian Foreign Ministry was in response
to a document on KPC signed in Pristina on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The document, which gives 200 representatives of the Kosovo
Protection Corps the right to hold weapons "for personal security",
was signed by KFOR Commander Michael Jackson, the U.N. secretary-
general's special envoy to Kosovo Bernard Kouchner, and a
representative of the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA).
</P>
<P>
"Earlier, we stated on many occasions that the preservation of
the inner organizational structure and vertical command of the
Kosovo Albanians' armed units, in whatever form, would be
extremely dangerous and inadmissible," the Interfax news agency
quoted the Russian statement as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The documents signed in Pristina go against the letter and
spirit of the U.N. Security Council Resolution 1244, under which
the KLA and other paramilitary groups of Kosovo Albanians must be
demilitarized," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement also expressed surprise over the name assigned
to the new organization.
</P>
<P>
Moscow also pointed to the fact that no KLA leader has
publicly rejected the plans to "reorganize the KLA into a "regular
" Kosovo armed force."
</P>
<P>
"A step in this particular direction has been made," the
Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Russia called for a full and final demilitarization of the KLA
as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"All measures must be taken to involve the former KLA in
peaceful life," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Otherwise, Russia, as an active participant in the Kosovo
settlement, will be unable to take up responsibility for the
possible negative consequences of this thoughtless political act,"
the statement emphasized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
