The mainland's 550,000 journalists were shocked to hear the
news, he said. They wanted to express their sympathy and
solicitude for their fellow journalists and stricken compatriots
in Taiwan and to extend condolences to the families of the victims
and to salute their fellow journalists working at the front, he
added.
</P>
