<HEADLINE> 3 Iraqis Start Trip Around World on Foot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Three Iraqis have kicked off
a round-the-world tour on foot to show the Iraqi people's
sufferings caused by the U.N. sanctions imposed on Iraq more than
nine years ago.
</P>
<P>
The travellers, including Mohammed Hussein ,11, Ali Hussein,
20 and Ahmed Muhiee Abdul-Waheed, 44, started their trek from the
southern Iraqi terminal Um Qasser, the Iraqi News Agency reported
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The trip is aimed at acquainting people around the world with
the blatant crimes committed by the U.S. and British governments
with their daily bombardment of Iraq's civil and service
facilities which had claimed lives of many civilians.
</P>
<P>
Since the U.S. and Britain launched four-day airstrikes
against Iraq last December, their warplanes have been regularly
attacking Iraqi civil and military targets in the no-fly zones,
causing severe civilian casualties and property damage.
</P>
<P>
The no-fly zones were imposed by the U.S. and Britain with a
claimed aim of protecting the Kurds in the north and the Shiite
Muslims in the south against possible attacks by Iraqi government
troops. 
</P>
