<HEADLINE> Full Text of Communique of 4th Plenum of CPC Central Committee (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was stressed at the plenum that strengthening and improving
the Party leadership are fundamental guarantees for speeding up
the reforms and development of State-owned enterprises and that
efforts must be made to establish a leading system for the State-
owned enterprises and an organizational and managerial system that
conform to the law of the market economy and China's actual
situation, improve the enterprise leadership, bring into play the
role of the Party organization of enterprises as their political
core, and adhere to the principle of relying on the working class
whole-heartedly. It is imperative to adhere and improve the
democratic management system with the worker representative
congress as the basic form. Efforts should be made to promote the
work of promoting ethical and cultural progress in enterprises and
to improve ideological and political work. Measures must be taken
to build a top-quality managerial team and standardize and improve
the ways of training, promoting, administrating, checking and
examining, and supervising management personnel, and create a
social environment for the healthy growth of the management
personnel and entrepreneurs. Party committees and governments at
all levels should firmly stand at the forefront of the reform,
emancipate their minds, be practical and realistic, start from the
actual situation of the State-owned enterprises of various trades,
unite with and lead the officials and people to press ahead
despite difficulties.
</P>
<P>
It was decided at the plenum that Comrade Hu Jintao was
appointed vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission (CMC),
and comrades Guo Boxiong and Xu Caihou were appointed CMC members.
</P>
<P>
Those attending the plenum discussed and approved "The Report
of the Central Commission for Discipline Inspection on the
Examination of the Xu Yunhong Question", and It was decided at
the plenum to dismiss Xu Yunhong from his position as an alternate
member of the CPC Central Committee and to expel him from the
Party. In view of the fact that some of Xu Yunhong's action have
violated the law, he will be dealt with by the judicial organs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990922.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full Text of Communique of 4th Plenum of CPC Central Committee (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The plenum held that the effort to improve the balance of debts
and assets and reduce the social burden of State-owned enterprises
need to be combined with that to deepen internal reforms,
establish new mechanisms, and increase scientific management. More
realistic and effective measures need to be found to solve
problems step by step in line with the macro-economic environment,
the State's financial ability and different circumstances, and
these measures should be designed to help State-owned enterprises
increase assets and reduce debts and to help them restructure
assets and debts. The social functions of enterprises need to be
separated and governments at various levels should support it
actively to ensure steady progress. Efforts should be continued to
reduce redundant employees and increase profits of enterprises,
deal with the re-employment of laid-off workers, maintain social
security, provide more opportunities for the jobless, direct
employment ideology, and develop a market-oriented employment
mechanism.
</P>
<P>
It was pointed out at the plenum that technological advancement
and industrial upgrading of State-owned enterprises needs to be
sped up to keep up with global industrial restructuring trends and
changes in domestic and overseas markets. With the market as a
guide, traditional industries need to be transformed with advanced
technology and technical transformation of the existing
enterprises needs to be strengthened with an aim to increase the
varieties of products, improve quality, and increase
profitability and exports. It is imperative that State-owned
enterprises take an important position in rising industries and
high-tech industries, getting hold of the core technologies and
playing a dominant role. Effective policies should be adopted to
ensure more investment in technical renovation in key industries,
key enterprises and key products. Efforts should be made to
establish a new system of technical renovation with enterprises as
its central consideration, promote cooperation between enterprises,
universities and research institutes, and help make research
results profitable. It is imperative to continue macro-economic
control and related reforms, keep a basic balance in the economy,
open the country wider to the outside world, improve the legal
system under the socialist market economy, develop various markets,
maintain economic order, and create a sound environment for the
reforms and development of State-owned enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
