<HEADLINE> 6 Germans Robbed by Gunmen in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Five unidentified armed men
took advantage of the big rallies in Metro Manila Tuesday and
robbed six German nationals of their valuables, the Philippine
News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An initial police report said the six Germans, whose names were
withheld pending thorough probe of the incident, were playing
billiards at about 4 p.m. local time when the robbers pounced on
them.
</P>
<P>
The robbery took place inside a sports center of the Lovim
Forcita Restaurant in Paranaque City of Metro Manila, where the
Germans were whiling their time away.
</P>
<P>
The suspects, armed with handguns and a hand grenade, announced
a holdup and herded the victims into a comfort room and divested
them of their jewelry and money worth 150,000 pesos (3,750 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The robbers later fled in a gateway vehicle. 
