<HEADLINE> IOC Official Expects Africa to Host Olympic Games in 10 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Jacques Rogge, an
International Olympic Committee (IOC) senior official, said in
Sydney on Wednesday he expected the Olympic Games to be held in
the African continent in the next 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Rogge, who is IOC commissioner for the 2000 Sydney Olympics,
said: "I am prepared to say that within a decade we will have the
Games in Africa."
</P>
<P>
No African city has ever held the Olympics. The South African
city of Cape Town was an unsuccessful bidder for the 2004 Olympic
Games while Cairo of Egypt is campaigning for 2008.
</P>
<P>
Rogge added that he would like to see the Games be held in
South America, saying "We would like to give the Games to Africa
and the same goes for South America."
</P>
<P>
Mexico City is the only Latin American city which has hosted
the Olympic Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
