<HEADLINE> Three Civilians Killed in Indian Shelling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 22 (Xinhua) -- At least three civilians
were killed and seven others injured Wednesday as a result of
Indian army's shelling across the Line of Control (LoC) in the
disputed area of Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani officials said Indian army resorted to unprovoked
heavy shelling simultaneously on scores of border villages in
Bhimbher district of Mirpur division in Pakistan-held Kashmir,
reported the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The killed were Tahira Bibi, 13, and Kashif Waseem, 9, in
border village Ghakhri of Baramula sub division, and Sughra Bibi
in Bandala village of Tahsil Samani.
</P>
<P>
Of the seven injured, four were in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
The Indian shelling also resulted in the damaging of several
houses and other properties in those villages, said the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
