<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The military, like all other
Nigerians, " want nothing short of true democracy in a united and
peaceful country," said Lt. Gen. Theophilus Danjuma, Nigeria's
Defense Minister Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But the civil populace, and not only the military, needs
reorientation if the nascent experiment in this country were to
blossom, the Guardian, a leading Nigerian newspaper Wednesday
quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
