 traceable to long years of military intervention in governance.
But there is need, he stressed, for partnership between civilians
and the military for intended professional restoration of the
institution to be accomplished.
</P>
<P>
The long military involvement in politics is an aberration, and
that is why strains and teething problems in the new civil rule
have been witnessed,
</P>
<P>
said Danjuma. So the drive for reorientation "should not be
limited to the military only."  
