<HEADLINE> Home Education Becoming Important Part Of Higher Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- An official from the Ministry
of Education (MOE) said today that home education has become an
important form of higher education in China and a useful way for
adults to get more education.
</P>
<P>
MOE statistics show about 31 million people taking examinations
at schools by the end of last year after learning higher education
courses at home. China has over 360 universities and colleges that
provide home education exams at schools.
</P>
<P>
The official said that home education has flourished after
China's reform and opening up and is a unique form of education
that combines self-teaching and society's help.
</P>
<P>
Scholars say that home education is a very versatile that
demands strong skills in the participants. The State Council last
year asked all of society to help establish an open education
system that includes study at home. 
