<DOCNO> XIE19990922.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CMC Vice-Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua)-- The following is the profile
of Hu Jintao, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission (
CMC) of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, male, Han nationality, is a native of Jixi, Anhui
Province, and was born in December 1942 (56 years old). He joined
the CPC in April 1964 and began to work in July 1965 when he
graduated from Qinghua University's Department of Hydraulic
Engineering and became an engineer.
</P>
<P>
He is now a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the 15th CPC Central Committee, vice-president of the
People's Republic of China, and a member of the Secretariat of the
15th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
He is also president of the Party School of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
From 1959 to 1965, he studied at Qinghua University majoring in
hydraulic engineering, and in 1964 he became a political
instructor at the university.
</P>
<P>
From 1965 to 1968, he did scientific research work at the
Hydraulic Engineering Department of Qinghua University and became
a political instructor (until the outbreak of the "Cultural
Revolution").
</P>
<P>
From 1968 to 1982, he worked in a housing construction team of
Liujiaxia Engineering Administration of the Ministry of Water
Resources and Electric Power.
</P>
<P>
Later he served as a technician, office secretary, and deputy
secretary of the general Party branch of the 813 sub-bureau of the
Fourth Engineering Bureau of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Then he worked as a secretary of the Gansu Provincial
Construction Commission, deputy head of the project design
management division of the construction commission, deputy
director of the commission, and secretary of the Gansu Provincial
Committee of the Communist Youth League of China (CYLC).
</P>
<P>
From 1982 to 1992, he became a member of the Secretariat of the
Central Committee of the CYLC, chairman of the All-China Youth
Federation, and the first secretary of the Secretariat of the CYLC
Central Committee, secretary of the Guizhou Provincial Committee
of the CPC and first secretary of the Party committee of the
Guizhou Provincial Military Area Command, and secretary of the CPC
Committee of the Tibet Autonomous Region and first secretary of
the Party committee of the Tibet Military Area Command.
</P>
<P>
From 1992 to present, he is a Standing Committee member of the
Political Bureau and member of the Secretariat of the 15th CPC
Central Committee; and president of the Party School of the CPC
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, he was elected vice-president of the People's Republic
of China.
</P>
<P>
Hu was an alternate member and member of the 12th CPC Central
Committee, and re-elected member of the 13th, 14th and 15th CPC
central committees.
</P>
<P>
Hu was elected a member of the Political Bureau, a member of
the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau and a member of the
Secretariat of the 14th and 15th CPC central committees.
</P>
<P>
Hu was also a member of the Standing Committee of the 6th
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
