<HEADLINE> URGENT: 4th Plenum of 15th CPC Central Committee Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The 4th Plenary Session of
the 15th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
was held in Beijing September 19-22, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Attending the plenum were 189 members of the CPC Central
Committee and 147 alternate members of the CPC Central Committee.
Members of the Standing Committee of the Central Commission for
Discipline Inspection and leading officials of related departments
attended as observers.
</P>
<P>
The plenum was presided over by the Political Bureau of the CPC
Central Committee. General Secretary Jiang Zemin of the CPC
Central Committee made an important speech at the plenum.
</P>
<P>
The plenum discussed and approved "A Decision of the CPC
Central Committee on Some Major Issues Concerning the Reform and
Development of State-Owned Enterprises."
</P>
<P>
The plenum spoke highly of the important role of the State-
owned enterprises in promoting China's economic and social
development and in consolidating the socialist system.
</P>
<P>
The plenum held that it is an important and urgent task to push
forward the reform and development of State-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
At present, the reform and development of State-owned
enterprises are at a crucial juncture, and some deep-rooted
contradictions and problems must be solved, and it is timely and
necessary for the plenum to concentrate on studying the problems
of the State-owned enterprises, according to the plenum.
</P>
<P>
The plenum decided on the major targets of State-owned
enterprises reform and development from now to the year of 2010
and the guiding principles that must be upheld.
</P>
<P>
It stressed that to fulfill the historic task, it is imperative
first of all to exert utmost efforts to realize the three-year
targets set for the State-owned enterprises to get out of
difficulties through reforms.
</P>
<P>
It was decided at the plenum that Hu Jintao was appointed vice-
chairman of the Central Military Commission, and Guo Boxiong (
commander of the Lanzhou Military Area Command) and Xu Caihou (
political commissar of the Jinan Military Area Command) were
appointed members of the Central Military Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
