<HEADLINE> Senior Party Official Expelled from CPC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Xu Yunhong, an alternate
member of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee, was
expelled from the CPC.
</P>
<P>
This was decided at the 4th Plenary Session of the 15th CPC
Central Committee which ended in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The plenum had examined and approved a report submitted by the
Central Commission for Discipline Inspection on the Xu case.
</P>
<P>
Xu was an alternate member of the CPC Central Committee, a
standing committee member of the CPC Zhejiang Provincial Committee
and secretary of the Ningbo City Party Committee, according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Xu, at the request of his son, helped the
business department of a Ningbo trust and investment company
obtain the qualifications for independent fund-raising, and his
son was given money and things for this, totaling to an equivalent
of more than 900,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Xu, again at the request of his son, ordered the Ningbo Daily
to buy the building of the Huahong International Center which is
of poor quality, and at the request of his wife, helped a Ningbo
firm to get loans by abusing his power. The firm now is not able
to repay its huge amount of loans.
</P>
<P>
The Central Discipline Inspection Commission holds that Xu, as
a senior Party official, abused his power time and again for the
benefits of his wife and son, causing big economic loss to the
Party and State and very bad political influence, and seriously
violating the Party discipline.
</P>
<P>
As some of what Xu had done has violated the law, his case
should be dealt with by judicial departments according to law, the
plenum said in a communique.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
