<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Adopt Examination System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- A Public Security Ministry
official said today that China's police departments have begun
using a competitive system to improve the level of police officers.
</P>
<P>
He said that the public security bureau in the city of Yangquan
in Shanxi Province has begun using a qualification test in its
personnel system for middle-level officers and 21 police officers
were relieved of their duties when they failed the tests, which
include a physical examination and colleagues' opinion.
</P>
<P>
Another official said that the exam will be given every five
years and will push police officers to improve their ability
overall. Eventually, an employment contract system will be
introduced to accompany the exam system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
