<HEADLINE> Demographic Facts About Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The following are the
demographic facts of Nepal listed in the State of World
Population, 1999 report released here Wednesday by the United
Nations Population Fund.
</P>
<P>
--Population in 1998: 21.8431 million, of which 10.9035 million
are male and 10.94 million are female.
</P>
<P>
--Functional age group in 1998: child (0-14) at 41.27%; youth
(15-24) at 19.15%; elderly (60+) at 5.49%; percentage of women
aged 15-19 at 47.91%.
</P>
<P>
--Population density in 1998: 148.41 per sq. km.
</P>
<P>
--Age at first marriage in 1996: 17.1 years.
</P>
<P>
--Annual population growth rate from 1996 to 2001: 2.37
percent.
</P>
<P>
--Crude birth rate(/1000) in 1998: 34.54.
</P>
<P>
--Crude death rate(/1000) in 1998: 10.74.
</P>
<P>
--Total fertility rate(/woman) in 1998: 4.43.
</P>
<P>
--Contraceptive prevalence rate between 15 and 49 years old in
1996: 29%.
</P>
<P>
--Child mortality rate in 1996: 43/1000.
</P>
<P>
--Infant mortality rate in 1996: 78.5/1000.
</P>
<P>
--Life expectancy at birth in 1998: 57.52.
</P>
<P>
--Birth not attended by health professionals in 1996: 89.9%.
</P>
<P>
--Adult literacy rate in 1996: 36.72% in average; 54.32% for
male; 21.33% for female; mean years of schooling at 2.254.
</P>
<P>
--Per capita income in 1996: NRs.7673 (about 130 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
--Allocation during the 8th development plan period: 13% for
education; 4.1% for health. 
</P>
</TEXT>
