<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Voices Response to Mayon's Eruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a press statement released here, Executive Secretary Ronaldo
Zamora said the Regional Disaster Coordinating Council in Albay
province on the southern tip of Luzon Island has been activated.
</P>
<P>
"We have been preparing for this," Zamora said after a meeting
of a caretaker committee tasked by Philippine President Joseph
Estrada to monitor and recommend actions on critical national
issues.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology
(Phivolcs) said that Mt. Mayon exhibited a sudden "phreatic
explosion" at 11:45 local time Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Phivolcs said the volcano's activity Wednesday morning was
recorded as an "explosion quake" lasting for about four minutes.
</P>
<P>
The ash column resulting from the eruption, according to
Phivolcs, reached as high as five to six kilometers above the
summit of the volcano and drifted to the northeast, east and
southeast.
</P>
<P>
Zamora said Defense Secretary Orlando Mercado, who is also
chairman of the National Disaster Coordinating Council, has
already made necessary arrangements to ensure that measures are in
place to prepare for any eventually arising from Mt. Mayon's
explosion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
