<HEADLINE> Dengue Claims 10 Lives in Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Cases of dengue fever have
risen to 412 in the northern Philippine province of Pangasinan
including 10 deaths, local authorities said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Provincial Health Officer Alyle Ochotorena earlier said she may
declare the province under dengue outbreak if the cases reached
450.
</P>
<P>
All the 10 fatalities were children aged from 3 to 15,
Philippine News Agency quoted her as saying.
</P>
<P>
Noting the latest report on dengue cases, Governor Victor
Agbayani reminded the public anew to take all the necessary
precautions to avoid the disease until the rainy season is over.
</P>
<P>
"Dengue fever is a deadly disease but it is preventable,"
Agbayani said as he called on community officials to undertake
massive clean-up campaign in their respective localities and
schools.
</P>
<P>
Ochotorena said the provincial health office had been
conducting massive information campaign on the nature, cure and
prevention of dengue fever. 
</P>
</TEXT>
