<HEADLINE> Japan Donates 10 million Yen To Chinese Foundation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- There was a ceremony in
Beijing today for a Japanese donation of 10 million yen to the
Foundation for Underdeveloped Regions in China.
</P>
<P>
A Foundation official says that the fund will be used to help
build three primary schools in underdeveloped counties in Jiangxi,
Guizhou, and Henan provinces, which can accommodate 1,350 pupils.
</P>
