<HEADLINE> India's NSE to Offer Net Trading from December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- India's National Stock
Exchange (NSE) will offer Internet-based stock trading facility in
the country from December, according to a NSE official.
</P>
<P>
Ravi Narain, NSE's deputy managing director, said in Calcutta
Tuesday, "Whether the e-commerce legislation is put in place or
not, we are going to start Internet-based trading within three
months from now."
</P>
<P>
If things go as planned, retail investors can place their
purchase and sell deals on the net in three months. The order will
be automatically executed by the broker through a recognized stock
exchange.
</P>
<P>
The system has benefits for both investors and brokers. The
inter-mediaries will be able to accept small orders from a large
number of retail or even institutional investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
