<HEADLINE> Chinese Red Cross Rescue Team Ready to Head for Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Red Cross Society of
China (RCSC) said today they are ready to send a team to provide
disaster relief to the victims of the Taiwan earthquake.
</P>
<P>
"We're contacting the Taiwan Red Cross organization, and we're
ready to send a team to join rescue efforts in Taiwan's disaster
areas a moment's notice," said an official with the RCSC, adding
that the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent
Societies will join the team as well.
</P>
<P>
He said, "we'll try our best to provide humanitarian aid to our
Taiwan compatriots. We'll try to provide anything they need."
</P>
<P>
Preparations for relief materials have been started by
provincial Red Cross Societies in southeast China and these
materials can be sent to Taiwan immediately, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
