<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Telephone Calls to Taiwan Soar after Quake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Telephone calls from Beijing
to Taiwan soared to 510,000 between 7:00 a.m. on Tuesday and 7:00
a.m. Wednesday after an earthquake measuring 7.6 on the Richter
Scale jolted Taiwan early yesterday morning.
</P>
<P>
The number of telephone calls was five times the average daily
volume, according to the Beijing International Telecommunications
Center.
</P>
<P>
The center has adopted measures to ensure the smooth operation
of the circuits between Beijing and Taiwan, however, only one-
tenth of the attempted calls were put through because of the
serious damage to telecommunications equipment in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest reports, the powerful quake has killed
more than 1,700 people and injured over 4,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
