<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kostov: Join A Single Europe, Solve Problems Between Bulgaria, Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 21 (Xinhua) -- To solve the problems between
Bulgaria and Macedonia is for them to join a single Europe,
Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan Kostov said after meeting with his
Macedonian counterpart Ljubco Georgievski Tuesday in Blagoevgrad,
Southwestern Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
He said that skepticism of the implementation of the Stability
Pact for Southeastern Europe is growing and may even turn into
disappointment, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
"Both Georgievski and I are with boosted self-confidence
because of the role, which our countries played in overcoming one
of the most serious conflicts in Southeastern Europe and in
establishing a policy of cooperation and not of confrontation in
the region," said Kostov.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria will support Macedonia's efforts for speeding up
integration into the European Union, said Kostov.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Georgievski said that several months ago, the two
countries began creating a spirit of trust by overcoming their
dispute over the use of language.
</P>
<P>
He added under an agreement of military aid, Bulgaria will give
Macedonia 94 tanks and other equipment, of which the first two
shipments have already arrived in Macedonia and the rest is to be
sent by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Without regional cooperation there can be no Euro-Atlantic
integration, stressed Georgievski.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an Agreement on free trade between Bulgaria and
Macedonia is expected to be signed on October 13 and enter into
force on January 1, next year, said Bulgarian Trade Minister
Valentin Vassilev after meeting with his Macedonian counterpart
Nikola Gruevski.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria will support Macedonia in signing similar agreement
with the Central European Free Trade Agreement (CEFTA) and the EU,
he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
