<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, September 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The European Union (EU) and Mexico will begin
their eighth round of trade talks on October 7, said a spokesman
from the EU Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here from Brussels, the meeting
was scheduled to be held in Mexico on September 27, but was
postponed because the EU are still analyzing their proposal. A
spokesman from the European Commission said that the Europeans
want the next meeting to be "substantial" now that they have
planned to make a definitive agreement in their negotiations with
Mexico before the end of 1999. (Mexico-EU-Trade Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- World Bank President Jim Wolfensohn called here
Tuesday for intensifying the fight against poverty as the world is
entering into a new millennium.
</P>
<P>
As the economic statistics are a lot better in East Asia this
year, "the thing that is of still deepest concern to us is that
the poverty levels are so high," Wolfensohn said at a press
conference before the start of the annual meetings of the World
Bank and the International Monetary Fund (IMF). (World Bank-
Poverty)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazil has the intellectual, scientific and
technological capabilities to face the challenges of the
globalization of the economy, said President Fernando Henrique
Cardoso on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has a highly developed scientific and technological
system, he said, citing as examples the country's deep-water
exploration of petroleum, the technologically sophisticated
national fleet of airplanes and a high agricultural productivity
of Brazilian companies in the central-eastern zone of the country.
Cardoso made the statement during an opening ceremony of the
Economic Session of the Brazilian-Portuguese Congress for year
2000 held here. (Brazil-Globalization-Preparation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- China and the World Bank signed an agreement here
Tuesday on China's donation of 500,000 U.S. dollars to the Asem-EU
Asian Financial Crisis Response Fund (Asem Trust Fund). 
</P>
</TEXT>
