<HEADLINE> Exit Poll Shows Big NDA Lead in Indian Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- An exit poll conducted for
the Star News TV channel has given the BJP-led National Democratic
Alliance (NDA) a big lead over the Congress in India's Lok Sabha
elections.
</P>
<P>
Telecast Tuesday night, the poll, conducted by "Insight" on
behalf of the news channel, gave the NDA 213 of the 344 seats
which have gone to the polls in the first three phases.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Congress and its allies finished far behind at
only 90, while the tally of other parties was put at 30.
</P>
<P>
This forecast, based on the biggest sample survey claimed by
any agency carrying out exit polls of about 125,000 voters spread
over 127 constituencies, is in complete contrast to those telecast
over Doordarshan and Jain TV recently. The projection is actually
for 333 seats out of the total 344.
</P>
<P>
In contrast to this rosy projection, another exit poll,
conducted by the Lokmat group of newspapers and released Tuesday,
gave the NDA only 169 out of the 344 seats.
</P>
<P>
It gave the Congress and its allies 159 seats -- by far the
best news for the Congress in any opinion poll thus far.
</P>
<P>
It said there is a 7.7-percent swing in favor of the Congress
as against only 1.5 percent for the NDA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
