<HEADLINE> Delegations Arrive in Beijing for National Ethnic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Most members of the 34
participating delegations have arrived in the Chinese capital for
the Beijing venue's competitions of China's Sixth National Games
of Traditional Ethnic Sports opening on Friday.
</P>
<P>
China is a multi-national country with a total population of 1.
1 billion. Besides the largest nationality the Hans, there are 55
minority nationalities covering some nine percent of the country's
population.
</P>
<P>
The national ethnic games are held every four years, with the
traditional sports of the ethnic minorities as competition and
demonstration events.
</P>
<P>
Lhasa, capital city of the Tibet Autonomous Region, and Chinese
capital city of Beijing had been chosen as the venues for the
Sixth National Ethnic Games. Competitions for the Lhasa venue
were held August 18-23 this year, with the participation of 1,200
athletes.
</P>
<P>
Expected to participate in the week-long Beijing competitions
are some 4,500 athletes from various Chinese provinces,
municipalities, autonomous regions and the Chinese army PLA.
</P>
<P>
On the Games program are a total of 13 medal events and some
200 demonstration events. The athletes are from all of the
country's 56 nationalities.
</P>
<P>
And, all the participants of the Beijing events have been
invited to attend the grand parade and other celebrations for the
50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China,
which falls on October 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
