<HEADLINE> Colombian-Venezuelan Border Remains Blocked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian-
Venezuelan border has been blocked in Colombia's La Guajira
province, since businessmen and indigenous people obstructed the
area to protest against the restriction of selling illegal
Venezuelan petroleum in the past four days.
</P>
<P>
Traders and indigenous people have set up barriers on the
border area after Colombia's National Customs and Tax Division
confiscated 26 trucks loaded with Venezuelan petroleum to supply
the north-east of Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan oil is sold at half the price of the Colombian
oil product in the black market in the border zones.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian Petroleum Company estimates that about 20,000
illegal barrels of Venezuelan petroleum are sold daily there.
</P>
<P>
Governor of the La Guajira province, Alvaro Cuello, proposed
that the Colombian Petroleum Company import the Venezuelan
petroleum directly and then deliver it to the local people and oil
traders.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian company announced Tuesday to send gasoline to La
Guajira to meet the demand of local people who are affected by the
protest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
