<HEADLINE> Vandenbroucke Wins Tour of Spain 16th stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Belgium's Frank Vandenbroucke
cliamed victory in the 16th stage of the Tour of Spain over 200.4
kms between Valencia and Teruel on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Cofidis rider clocked in five hours 20 minutes 41 seconds,
after tracking the back wheel of Spain's Jon Odriozola and taking
off 250 meters from the line.
</P>
<P>
The pair made a break 55 kms from the finish and, after sharing
the pace-making, came home more than four and a half minutes ahead
of a five-man group who had been part of an initial escape early
in the race.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Jan Ullrich retained the race leader for a fifth
successive day after finishing nearly 13 minutes behind the winner.
</P>
