<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pistons Acquire Guard Derek Harper from Lakers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The Detroit Pistons,
looking to add depth at point guard, acquired aging Derek Harper
from the Los Angeles Lakers for the rights to rookie forward
Melvin Levett on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The move comes one day after Detriot brought back free agent
forward Terry Mills, another veteran who played with the Pistons
from 1992-1997.
</P>
<P>
"Derek gives us the backup point guard we've been looking for,"
Detriot executive vice president and general manager Rick Sund
said. "He's been in the league for 16 seasons and has played at a
high level his entire career."
</P>
<P>
The 37-year-old Harper is tied with Eddie Johnson atop the
active list in games played with 1,119 and is the only player in
NBA history to register more than 16,000 points, 6,500 assists and
1,900 steals.
</P>
<P>
However, Harper's game has slipped in recent years and he
averaged just 6.9 points in 45 games for Los Angeles last season,
his lowest output since averaging 5.7 points as a rookie with the
Dallas Mavericks in 1983-84.
</P>
<P>
"He was brought to LA last season primarily as a backup and he
ended up starting more than half of their games," Sund said. "
Derek has been honored several times in his career for his defense
and he can contribute to this team."
</P>
<P>
Harper started 29 games but did not provide the leadership the
Lakers were looking for and lost his starting job down the stretch
to third-year guard Derek Fisher.
</P>
<P>
The addition of Levett continues Lakers vice president Jerry
West's recent trend of acquiring players from the University of
Cincinnati. The Pistons chose Levett 54th overall in the 1999
draft.
</P>
<P>
Harper, who has career averages of 13.3 points and 5.5 assists,
ranks seventh on the all-time steals list with 1,957 and 10th in 3-
point attempts with 3,026.
</P>
<P>
Among active players, Harper stands third in assists (6,577),
fifth in minutes played and 10th in shot attempts. He was named to
the NBA All-Defensive team in 1987 and 1990.
</P>
<P>
Selected 11th overall by the Mavericks in 1983, Harper also has
played with the New York Knicks, Orlando Magic and Lakers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
