<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Daei Double Beats Chelsea in Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- One goal in each half from
Iranian striker Ali Daei helped Hertha Berlin beat Chelsea 2-1 in
a Champions League group H match on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hertha, playing their first European match in front of their
own fans since their UEFA Cup semifinal exit to Red Star Belgrade
20 years ago, moved in front after two minutes when Daei headed
home from a Tony Sanneh cross.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea dominated the game in the second half but without
creating clear chances and in the 70th minute a mistake from
French defender Frank Leboeuf set up Daei for his second goal.
</P>
<P>
Bayern Munich was another team from Germany which remained
unbeaten in the Champions League with a last minute equalizer at
Ranger of Scotland.
</P>
<P>
Bayern, who lost 2-1 to Manchester United in last season's
dramatic final in Barcelona after conceding two goals in the last
two minutes of the match, staged their own late revival at Ibrox.
</P>
<P>
An 89th minute shot from Michael Tarnat took a deflection off
his Paraguayan team mate Roque Santa Cruz, wrong-footed the
goalkeeper and gave Bayern a 1-1 draw with the Scottish champions
in Group F.
</P>
<P>
Including last week's matches, the four German teams Bayern,
Hertha Borussia Dortmund and Bayer Leverkusen have now played six
matches in the Champions League between them and none of them have
lost a game with two wins and four draws.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, the three English teams Manchester United, Arsenal
and Chelsea, have played four matches between them and have yet to
win a game after three draws and a defeat.
</P>
<P>
The other match in Group F also ended in a 1-1 draw between PSV
Eindhoven and Valencia, leaving Valencia and Bayern at the top of
the standings with four points from two matches and PSV and
Rangers both on one.
</P>
<P>
In Group H, AC Milan beat Galatasaray 2-1 to move on to four
points with Hertha. Both Galatasaray and Chelsea have one point
from their opening two matches.
</P>
<P>
Porto maintained their 100 per cent start in Group E with a 2-0
win over Olympiakos while Real Madrid crushed Molde of Norway 4-1
in front of only 15,000 fans at the Santiago Bernabeu Stadium --
the lowest crowd to watch a Champions League match there.
</P>
<P>
Porto, the only team to have played two matches and not to have
dropped a point or conceded a goal, have six points with Real on
four, Olympiakos on one and Molde none after two defeats.
</P>
<P>
Spartak Moscow top group G despite being held to a 1-1 draw at
home by Sparta Prague and having two players sent off.
</P>
<P>
Their 3-1 victory at Willem II Tilburg last week means they
edge Girondins Bordeaux, who also have four points after their
exciting 3-2 win over Willem II on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
