<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tang Jiaxuan Meets Iranian Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The two sides had an extensive exchanges of views on the
development of bilateral relations and on international and
regional issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
With a positive assessment of the development of the China-Iran
relationship, the two foreign ministers stressed that further
developing bilateral friendly relations and cooperation not only
represents the aspiration of the two peoples, but also accords with
the fundamental interests of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides indicated that friendly exchanges in all areas
between the two countries will be encouraged.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to establish a mechanism of regular
consultations between the two ministries of foreign affairs and
decided to hold the Tenth Session of the China-Iran Joint
Commission on Economic, Trade, scientific and Technological
Cooperation in Beijing this year.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the two foreign ministers discussed international
issues of mutual concern. The two sides stood for establishing
a multi-polar world and settling inter-state disputes through
peaceful negotiations, and approved of conducting dialogue
between different civilizations, so as to maintain world peace
and promote common development.
</P>
<P>
The two sides advocated the establishment of a fair and
equitable new international political and economic order on the
basis of the principles of mutual respect for sovereignty and
territorial integrity, mutual non-aggression, non-interference in
each others' internal affairs, equality and mutual benefit,
peaceful co-existence, the U.N. Charter and other
universally-accepted norms governing international relations.
</P>
