<HEADLINE> Colombian Rebels Deny Links to Homicide of Mayor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The Revolutionary
Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) on Tuesday denied responsibility
for the death of Marco Emilio Londono, Mayor of Vistahermosa,
central-eastern of the country.
</P>
<P>
Vistahermosa is one of the five municipals of the demilitarized
zones created since November 7, 1998 for the peace talks by the
government.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the eastern block of the FARC denied what it
considered "slanderous accusation" made by the military chief.
</P>
<P>
Londono was assacinated last Sunday in Villavicencio, where he
had taken refuge after receiving death threats.
</P>
<P>
Omar Garcia, the mayor of San Vicente del Caguan, in the
demilitarized zone, recently said that he has received death
threats from groups believed to be sympathetic to the guerrilla
cause.  
