<HEADLINE> China Donates 500,000 Dollars to Asem Trust Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- China and the World Bank
signed an agreement here Tuesday on China's donation of 500,000
U.S. dollars to the Asem-EU Asian Financial Crisis Response Fund
(Asem Trust Fund).
</P>
<P>
Liu Xiaoming, Charge'd Affairs of the Chinese Embassy in the
United States and Vice President of the World Bank Motoo Kusakabe
signed the agreement.
</P>
<P>
"China supports the creation of the Asem Trust Fund," Liu
Xiaoming said. "We hope the timely technical assistance through
the Trust Fund will facilitate the recovery of the Asian countries
affected by the financial crisis."
</P>
<P>
During the second Asia-Europe Meeting (Asem) held in London in
1998, the Asem leaders decided to create the Asem Trust Fund at the
World Bank to help the eligible Asian countries to recover from
the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan announced China's
decision to donate 500,000 dollars for the Fund at the second Asem
Foreign Ministers Meeting in March this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
