<HEADLINE> Albright Plans to Meet Syrian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright planned to meet Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq
al-Shara on Wednesday in an effort to find a way to restart
long-stalled Syria-Israel peace negotiations, a U.S. official said
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Albright would like to see "whether there can be a formula
established to restart the negotiations" when she meets the
Syrian foreign minister on the fringes of the annual opening of
the U.N. General Assembly where leaders and foreign ministers
from most countries converge on U.N. headquarters in New York,
the official said.
</P>
<P>
She will also "try to ensure that if the peace talks are
restarted, there will be an ability to move quickly through the
myriad issues," he said.
</P>
<P>
The official refused to predict how close Israel and Syria
are to resuming the peace negotiations. "It's an extraordinarily
difficult exercise," he said.
</P>
<P>
Albright was also scheduled to hold separate talks on
Wednesday with Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa.
</P>
<P>
"We think they (Egyptians) are going to continue to play an
important role, especially in the permanent status talks"
between Israel and the Palestinians, the official said. 
</P>
